===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|攸|木|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s}}. Originally it indicates a small branch, perhaps with some reference to a wooden stick (in the top component, there is a man warned by a hand holding a vertical stick). The bottom part of the character is unrelated to [[茶]].

===Etymology===
Related to {{och-l|悠|remote; distant}}, {{och-l|修|long and thin}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

